    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>St. David's Episcopal Church was established on Passion Sunday, March 27th, 1955 as a parochial mission of Christ Episcopal Church of Dearborn. The Very Reverend Jon Weaver, Dean of St. Paul's Cathedral, Detroit, MI, presided. Services were held in the gymnasium of the Garden City Memorial School until 1957, when the congregation broke ground for the construction of a new church home at 27500 Marquette.</p>
      <p>The parish was admitted to union with the Diocese of Michigan on May 15th, 1964, ending its role as a parochial mission of Christ Episcopal Church, Dearborn, MI. On November 29th, 1964, the Very Reverend Thomas Smith installed the Reverend Fred Nicholson as the first Rector of St. David's.</p>
      <p>The Congregation was dissolved on May 15th, 2005. Leadership cited dwindling attendance aggravated by the 2003 General Convention's consent to the election of Gene Robinson as Bishop in New Hampshire. The congregation's attendance had dwindled from an average of 300 in 1965 to about 35 per week by the end of 2003. The remaining congregation reinvented itself as the Journey of Faith Church and moved to a new location at the Garden City Maplewood Community Center.</p>
